What you need to know:

Last week, some took to the streets of Nairobi to protest delayed pay even after the ministry said it had released funds.Headteacher Lucy Apondi said lack of finances is a huge challenge to the school with 1,316 pupils accommodated in 28 classrooms.Kagumo High School chief principal Cyrus Mwirigi said there was need to revise the school timetable to accommodate the new normal.